  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Mechanical & Electrical (M&E) Engineer",
  "description": "<p>Responsibilities:- </p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Develop M&amp;E system designs (HVAC, plumbing, fire protection, lighting, power distribution, etc.).</li>\n  <li>Prepare technical drawings, specifications, and calculations.</li>\n  <li>Coordinate with architects, structural engineers, and other consultants.</li>\n  <li>Conduct feasibility studies </li>\n  <li>Manage the implementation of M&amp;E systems during construction.</li>\n  <li>Monitor project timelines, budgets, and resources.</li>\n  <li>Coordinate with contractors, suppliers, and site teams.</li>\n  <li>Ensure materials and workmanship meet design specs and standards.and cost estimates.</li>\n  <li>Supervise M&amp;E works on-site to ensure proper installation.</li>\n  <li>Perform inspections and testing of systems (e.g., electrical wiring, ventilation).</li>\n  <li>Identify and resolve technical or coordination issues on-site.</li>\n  <li>Ensure compliance with local codes, safety regulations, and international standards.</li>\n  <li>Review risk assessments and method statements.</li>\n  <li>Implement safety procedures related to mechanical and electrical works.</li>\n  <li>Oversee commissioning processes for M&amp;E systems.</li>\n  <li>Verify that systems operate as intended before handover.</li>\n  <li>Troubleshoot and rectify faults found during testing.</li>\n  <li>Provide input into facility management and maintenance plans.</li>\n  <li>Assist in diagnosing and resolving M&amp;E issues in existing buildings.</li>\n  <li>Recommend system upgrades or energy-efficient solutions.</li>\n  <li>Maintain detailed project documentation and progress reports.</li>\n  <li>Prepare as-built drawings and operation &amp; maintenance manuals.</li>\n  <li>Attend coordination meetings and provide technical input.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Requirement:- </p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Bachelor Degree in related fileds</li>\n  <li>At least 3 years related experience </li>\n  <li>Familiar with Design Software, project management tools and etc </li>\n</ul>",
